  abstract     = {Genetics education affects how students explain racial
                  inequality. For example, when students learn about race during
                  Mendelian genetics, they believe more strongly that racial
                  inequality is genetically determined. In contrast, studies
                  tentatively suggest that if students learn about the
                  complexity of genomics and race it can reduce this same
